==English==
===Transitive verb===
'''to [[rule]] [[out]]'''

#To cross (something) out by drawing a straight line through it, often by using a ruler.
#To reject (an option or possibility).
#:''As John Doe had an alibi, the police were able to rule him out as a suspect.''

====Synonyms====
*(''cross out''): [[cross out]], [[delete]]
*(''reject''): [[eliminate]], [[reject]]

====Antonyms====
*(''reject''): [[consider]], [[rule in]]